Candidates are pushed into these collections via `ProbeContext::push_candidate()` (line 781). Each `Candidate<'tcx>` struct wraps a `ty::AssocItem` along with metadata like import IDs and candidate kind.

The core candidate evaluation happens in `ProbeContext::consider_candidates()` (line 1676), which filters candidates and applies various resolution rules including the shadowing and subtrait logic at lines 1707-1737. When multiple candidates remain after filtering at line 1707, the code attempts to collapse them via `collapse_candidates_to_trait_pick()` and `collapse_candidates_to_subtrait_pick()`. If collapse fails and multiple candidates remain, line 1741 returns `MethodError::Ambiguity(sources)`.

